load ../contradiction-reopener.maude

--- The corruption pattern: a contradiction flag minted by a single noisy
--- observation, or a flag that quietly revokes the human's answer.

--- Bite: a spiking-but-receding posterior (up;down;up;down) never flags
--- under the sound sustained trigger, in any interleaving.
search [1] in WHIPPLESCRIPT-CONTRADICTION-REOPENER :
  sound watching streak(z) stream(up ; down ; up ; down ; nilM)
  =>* flagged RESIDUAL:Cfg .

--- Hazard demonstrated: the naive spike trigger flags the very same
--- stream on the first movement.
search [1] in WHIPPLESCRIPT-CONTRADICTION-REOPENER :
  naive watching streak(z) stream(up ; down ; up ; down ; nilM)
  =>* flagged RESIDUAL:Cfg .

--- Coverage: three consecutive tightenings raise the advisory flag.
search [1] in WHIPPLESCRIPT-CONTRADICTION-REOPENER :
  sound watching streak(z) stream(up ; up ; up ; nilM)
  =>* flagged RESIDUAL:Cfg .

--- Bite: the flag is advisory only -- the reopener has no path to
--- `revoked`, even from a fully flagged state with standing authority.
search [1] in WHIPPLESCRIPT-CONTRADICTION-REOPENER :
  sound watching answered streak(z) stream(up ; up ; up ; nilM)
  =>* revoked RESIDUAL:Cfg .

--- Coverage: a reset streak that re-tightens still flags -- recession
--- delays the reopener, never disables it.
search [1] in WHIPPLESCRIPT-CONTRADICTION-REOPENER :
  sound watching streak(z) stream(up ; down ; up ; up ; up ; nilM)
  =>* flagged RESIDUAL:Cfg .
